                  </persName>
            . I am the prisoner's brother. I called at my father's, where he lived, about half-past seven o'clock in the evening - my father was in bed; I saw this box broken open, and went to look for the prisoner, but could not find him - I returned, and found him on the stairs - we went up stairs together; I accused him of taking the things, and said he had better tell - I found the duplicates on my father's bed.</p>
               <p>JOHN WILLIAM HARRISON. I apprehended the prisoner in Half Moon-passage - he said nothing to the charge.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
